      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Software used for CFD simulation shall be sufficiently documented and controlled to support credible results.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent v2022R2 was used under a validated installation with version-controlled case files. Basic SQA documentation confirming software version and license traceability was provided, meeting the Gradation 1 requirement for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver correctness shall be demonstrated through benchmark test cases relevant to internal rotating flow.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent has been verified against standard internal flow benchmarks published by the vendor. Code verification at Gradation 1 is satisfied by reference to established solver validation documentation for rotating machinery applications."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "A mesh convergence study shall demonstrate that discretization error in the hemolysis index QoI is below 5% between successive refinement levels.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted (1.2M, 3.8M, 9.1M cells). The hemolysis index QoI changed by 3.2% between the medium and fine meshes, satisfying the 5% convergence criterion. The medium mesh was selected for production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation shall correspond to at least 3 of the 5 target flow-speed operating points within ±5% of nominal values.",
      "rationale": "FDA experimental data for the generic centrifugal pump was collected at 5 flow-speed combinations (2.5 L/min at 2500 RPM through 6 L/min at 3500 RPM). All 5 points were reproduced in the validation experiments within ±3% of nominal flow and ±1% of nominal speed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted hemolysis index values shall agree with experimental measurements within 15% across all validated operating points.",
      "rationale": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values were compared against published FDA experimental results at all 5 operating points. Maximum deviation was 11.4% at the 6 L/min, 3500 RPM condition. All other points showed deviations below 9%, satisfying the 15% criterion."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoIs used in validation (NIH, shear stress distribution) shall directly correspond to the decision-relevant outputs for the CPB hemolysis COU.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis, which directly maps to the clinical decision criterion of RH < 1 relative to the predicate device. Shear stress exposure time integral is used as a secondary QoI to confirm mechanistic consistency. Both QoIs are directly relevant to the COU decision."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities shall use the same pump geometry family and overlapping operating conditions as the COU device.",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump, which shares the same impeller-volute topology as the target CPB device. Operating conditions in the validation study span the full COU operating envelope. Geometric and functional similarity supports direct relevance of validation evidence to the COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence of residuals to below 1e-5 shall be demonstrated for all simulations.",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error is not assessed at MRL 2 for this factor. Residual convergence monitoring was performed as standard practice and logs are retained, but formal Gradation 1 assessment is not required at this risk level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup shall be reviewed by a qualified analyst independent of the primary simulation engineer.",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment is not required at MRL 2. Simulation setup was performed by an experienced CFD engineer with blood pump modeling background. Independent review was not formally conducted but is not mandated at this model risk level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The selected turbulence model and hemolysis damage model shall be justified by reference to published literature for similar rotating blood-contacting devices.",
      "rationale": "Model form assessment is not required at MRL 2. The SST k-omega turbulence model and Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model were selected based on prevalent use in blood pump CFD literature. Formal model form uncertainty quantification was not performed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Blood viscosity and density inputs shall be sourced from peer-reviewed references and documented in the simulation record.",
      "rationale": "Model inputs assessment is not required at MRL 2. Blood properties (density 1060 kg/m3, dynamic viscosity 0.0035 Pa·s) were taken from standard physiological references. Input uncertainty propagation was not formally quantified."
    },
    {
